To draw a chessboard state represented by a Forsyth-Edwards Notation (FEN) in LaTeX, you can utilize the `chessfigures` package along with the `chessboard` package. The `chessfigures` package provides the necessary figures for the chess pieces, while the `chessboard` package allows you to construct a chessboard based on a FEN description.

Below is a step-by-step guide and a LaTeX code snippet that demonstrates how to include and use these packages to draw a chessboard based on a given FEN. For this example, let's consider a simple FEN string: `"rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"` which represents the starting position of a standard chess game.

### Step 1: Include Required Packages

First, include the necessary packages in the preamble of your LaTeX document. You'll need `chessboard` and `chessfigures`.

```latex
\usepackage{chessboard}
\usepackage{chessfigures}
```

### Step 2: Load Figures

Before drawing the board, load the chess figures using the `loadfigure` command. This step is crucial for displaying the actual pieces on the board.

```latex
\chessfigureload{png} % Specify the format of the figures (e.g., png, pdf)
```

### Step 3: Draw the Chessboard

With the packages included and the figures loaded, you can now draw the chessboard based on the FEN notation. Use the `ChessBoard` command followed by your FEN string within the document body.

```latex
\begin{center}
    \newchessgame
    \ChessBoard[boardstyle={utf8style}, size=200]{rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1}
\end{center}
```

- `boardstyle={utf8style}` is used for styling the board. You can adjust this according to your preference.
- `size=200` adjusts the size of the chessboard. Modify this value to fit your document layout.
- The `ChessBoard` command takes the FEN string as an argument.

### Complete LaTeX Code

Combining all the steps, here is a complete LaTeX document that includes a chessboard drawn from a FEN notation:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}
\usepackage{chessfigures}

\begin{document}

\title{Chessboard from FEN}
\author{Your Name}
\date{\today}
\maketitle

\begin{center}
    \newchessgame
    \chessfigureload{png} % Adjust based on the format of your figures
    \ChessBoard[boardstyle={utf8style}, size=200]{rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1}
\end{center}

\end{document}
```

